cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LT

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the decidability of language inclusion problem for a class of timed automata. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the construction of a deterministic timed automaton from a non-deterministic one. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with timed automata and their language properties. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) may be relevant as the paper discusses a method for computing the timestamp of a timed automaton. 
- cs.LT (Learning) may be relevant as the paper discusses the periodicity of the language of timed automata.
